Source: kerrighed
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Cyril Brulebois <cyril.brulebois@kerlabs.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7.0.50), autotools-dev, lsb-base, lsb-release, xmlto, pkg-config, chrpath, rsync, patchutils
Standards-Version: 3.8.0
Homepage: http://www.kerrighed.org/
XS-Kernel-Name: 2.6.30
XS-Kernel-Version: 3.0.0-1

Package: kerrighed
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 kerrighed-image-${kernel:Name} (>= ${kernel:Version}),
 kerrighed-tools (>= ${source:Version})
Description: The Kerrighed OS
 The Kerrighed OS is a Linux-based SSI system which allows you to use
 a cluster as a single SMP machine.
 .
 This package is a metapackage which depends on everything you need to run
 a Kerrighed cluster.

Package: kerrighed-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 kerrighed-image-${kernel:Name} (>= ${kernel:Version}),
 kerrighed-tools (>= ${source:Version}),
 kerrighed-headers-${kernel:Name} (>= ${kernel:Version}),
 libkerrighed-dev (>= ${source:Version})
Description: The Kerrighed OS - development version
 The Kerrighed OS is a Linux-based SSI system which allows you to use
 a cluster as a single SMP machine.
 .
 This package is a metapackage which depends on everything you need to run
 a Kerrighed cluster, including development packages.

Package: libkerrighed1
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Suggests: libkerrighed-dev (= ${binary:Version})
Description: The Kerrighed library
 The Kerrighed OS is a Linux-based SSI system which allows you to use
 a cluster as a single SMP machine.
 .
 This package contains the library required to use advanced features
 of the Kerrighed OS.

